Package gobblin.config.store.api

This package contains the config stores API for gobblin configuration management.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    ConfigKeyPath
    The ConfigKeyPath is used to describe the relative path for a given configuration key URI to the root URI of a config store (ConfigStore.getStoreURI()).
    ConfigStore
    The ConfigStore interface used to describe a configuration store.
    ConfigStoreFactory<T extends ConfigStore>
    ConfigStoreFactory is used to created ConfigStores.
    ConfigStoreWithBatchFetches
    ConfigStoreWithBatchFetches indicate this ConfigStore support (efficient) fetching of batches of config keys with the same config version.
    ConfigStoreWithImportedBy
    ConfigStoreWithImportedBy indicates that this ConfigStore implementation supports an efficient mapping from the config key to the config keys that directly import it (aka the imported-by relationship).
    ConfigStoreWithImportedByRecursively
    This is an extension of the ConfigStoreWithImportedBy interface which marks that this ConfigStore implementation supports not only efficiently obtaining the config keys that directly import a given config key but also the full transitive closure of such keys.
    ConfigStoreWithResolution
    The ConfigStoreWithResolution interface is used to indicate the ConfigStore implementation supports an efficient import configuration resolution for a given config key.
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    ConfigStoreCreationException  
    VersionDoesNotExistException  
  • Annotation Types Summary 
    Annotation Type Description
    ConfigStoreWithStableVersioning
    The ConfigStoreWithStableVersioning annotation is used to indicate that the configuration store supports stable versioning.

Package gobblin.config.store.api Description

This package contains the config stores API for gobblin configuration management. Configuration stores provide a low-level API for reading Config objects. These are generally accessed through the config client API.
